12	// correcting up to m losses. It is the residual-loss SLA the target_residual
13	// surface inverts (see (*Controller).residualTargetParity): D counts per-group
14	// losses, and any losses beyond the m the parity can repair are the residual. At
15	// p=0 the residual is 0 (no loss); at p=1 every shard is lost so the residual is
16	// max(0, k-m)/k.
17	//
18	// The binomial PMF is accumulated iteratively (pmf_0 = (1-p)^k, then the standard
19	// pmf_d = pmf_{d-1} * (k-d+1)/d * p/(1-p) recurrence) so no binomial coefficient is
20	// materialized, keeping it numerically stable for k up to the field limit.
